Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

I feel pretty strongly that unit tests should not be calling out to live resources like this, even if it's to openstack.org. And the problem with using file:// is that scheme is explicitly excluded for security reasons.

A possible solution might be to create a test-only store class using a special scheme like "test-file://". This store could be a fairly trivial subclass of the existing file store, just registered to this special scheme. Then the copy-from could point to one of the test images that the setup already creates.

Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

Eddie mentions a good point. A good way would be to do something like this https://review.openstack.org/#/c/91734/4/glance/tests/unit/test_store_base.py

Also, may be both the Merge Props can leverage the same dummy store.

Patch Set 4:

(1 comment)

I like that teststore idea. I would prefer as well the tests not sending requests out of the system they are being ran.
